s. We propose a Discrete Wavelet Transform (DWT)-based multi-resolution framework th...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.21070", "source": "arXiv NLP", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.21070v1/2604.21070v1/model.png", "score": 10}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2604.21045v1", "title": "Hierarchical Policy Optimization for Simultaneous Translation of Unbounded Speech", "summary": "Abstract: Simultaneous speech translation (SST) generates translations while receiving partial speech input. Recent advances show that large language models (LLMs) can substantially improve SST quality, but at the cost of high computational overhead. To reduce this cost, prior work reformulates SST ...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.21045", "source": "arXiv NLP", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.21045v1/2604.21045v1/x1.png", "score": 9}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2604.20983v1", "title": "Thinking Like a Botanist: Challenging Multimodal Language Models with Intent-Driven Chain-of-Inquiry", "summary": "Abstract: Vision evaluations are typically done through multi-step processes. In most contemporary fields, experts analyze images using structured, evidence-based adaptive questioning. In plant pathology, botanists inspect leaf images, identify visual cues, infer diagnostic intent, and probe further...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.20983", "source": "arXiv CV", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.20983v1/2604.20983v1/DIA_1.png", "score": 9}]}